# Little Logic Lab — always apply

Before architectural or product work, read and follow:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `docs/Vision.md`
- `docs/Architecture.md`
- `docs/Curriculum.md`

Also respect `docs/UI-Guidelines.md`, `docs/CodingStandards.md`, and `docs/DECISIONS.md`.

## Non-negotiables

- Teach reasoning, not memorization; never reveal answers (hints ask questions).
- No manipulative engagement / gamification (streaks, coins, leaderboards, pressure timers).
- App adapts to the child; progress = concept mastery; age is only a recommendation.
- Prefer simple, reusable, testable Flutter code; business logic outside UI; composition over inheritance.
- New puzzles: update `docs/Curriculum.md` first. Significant choices: append `docs/DECISIONS.md`.
- Do not add frameworks or product features without trade-offs.
